# shadcn/ui Usage

This project uses [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/) for all UI components. Never write custom UI primitives from scratch when a shadcn/ui component is available.

## Initialization

If shadcn/ui is not yet set up in the project:

```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest init -t next
```

## Adding Components

Install components on demand. Example for the `button` component:

```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button
```

Replace `button` with the desired component name (e.g. `card`, `dialog`, `input`, `table`, etc.).

## Rules

- Always check `components/ui/` before creating a new UI element — it may already be installed.
- If a needed component is not in `components/ui/`, add it via the CLI above rather than building it manually.
- Import components from `@/components/ui/<component>`, not from third-party libraries.
